ABUJA – The Nigerian Air Force (NAF) on Sunday warned that there would be movement of its aircraft at altitude beginning from Monday. This was contained in a statement by the headquarters, Nigerian Air Force, issued through Air Commodore Ibikunle Daramola, Director of Public Relations and Information (DOPRI). Daramola, in the statement said that the exercise was to herald the introduction of the Nigerian Air Force’s newly acquired Agusta 109E (M) Power Helicopters and an Mi-171 E Combat Helicopter on February 6 at the Eagle Square, Abuja. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network “Rehearsals for activities that form part of the induction ceremony will involve the movement of military aircraft flying at low level as from Monday, 3 to Thursday, 6 February 2020,” the Air force spokesman stressed. He requested members of the public not to panic but go about their normal businesses.